defs.docs:
Library holding necessary code for the Ribosome  that is also useful for hdk-rust,
 or more generally for making rust code that the Ribosome can run.
 Must not have any dependency with any other Holochain crates.

defs.name: api_serialization
defs.docs: ignore api_serialization because it is nothing but structs to hold serialization

defs.value: ZomeFnCallArgs { instance_handle, zome_name, cap_token, fn_name, fn_args }
defs.docs: Struct for input data received when Zome API function call() is invoked

defs.name: capabilities
defs.docs:
This module holds structs for all arguments and return types
 that get serialized and deserialized between core native and
 the WASM based ribosome.

defs.name: CommitEntryOptions
defs.docs: Structure used to specify additional options to a commit_entry_result call.

defs.name: CommitEntryArgs
defs.docs: The arguments required to execute a commit_entry_result() call.

defs.name: CommitEntryResult
defs.docs:
Represents any useful information to return after
 entries are committed

defs.name: EmitSignalArgs
defs.docs: Struct for input data received when invoke_emit_signal is called

defs.name: GetEntryOptions
defs.docs:
Structure used to specify what should be returned to a call to get_entry_result()
 The default is to return the latest entry.

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (status_request: StatusRequestKind, entry: bool, headers: bool, timeout: Timeout) -> Self

defs.name: GetEntryResultItem
defs.docs:
Structure that holds data returned from a get entry request.
 When the meta is None, we know the entry wasn't found.  This is
 because at the very least the entry_type and the address will be
 returned if nothing else was requested in the GetEntryOptions

defs.name: EntryHistory
defs.docs:
Structure that holds a whole crud status history if the status request
 in the GetEntryOptions was set to StatusRequestKind::All

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (request_kind: StatusRequestKind, maybe_entry_with_meta_and_headers: Option<(&EntryWithMeta, Vec<ChainHeader>)>) -> Self

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: clears the entry result to be equivalent to not found

defs.name: push
defs.docs: adds an item to history, or if Single, writes over the current value of the item

defs.name: latest
defs.docs:
returns the entry searched for.  Note that if the GetEntryOptions did not
 include a request for the entry value, this function will return None even if the
 entry was found.

Retrieve a stored string from an allocation.

defs.name: try_from_ribosome_encoding
defs.docs:
equivalent to TryFrom<RibosomeEncodingBits> for WasmAllocation
 not implemented as a trait because RibosomeEncodingBits is a primitive and that would couple
 allocations to ribosome encoding

defs.name: try_from_ribosome_encoding
defs.docs:
equivalent to TryFrom<RibosomeEncodingBits> for WasmStack
 not implemented as a trait because RibosomeEncodingBits is a primitive and that would couple
 stacks to ribosome encoding
 wraps WasmAllocation::try_from_ribosome_encoding internally but has a "higher level"
 return signature intended for direct use/return in/from ribosome fns

defs.name: return_code_for_allocation_result
defs.docs:
Equivalent to From<AllocationResult> for RibosomeEncodedValue
 not possible to implement the trait as Result and RibosomeEncodedValue from different crates
